3446 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3447 
3448 static void R__WriteDestructorBody(FILE *file, TIter &next)
3449 {
3450  TStreamerElement *element = 0;
3451  next.Reset();
3452  while ((element = (TStreamerElement*)next())) {
3453  if (element->GetType() == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObjectp || element->GetType() == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObjectP||
3454  element->GetType() == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kAnyp || element->GetType() == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kAnyP
3455  || element->GetType() == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kAnyPnoVT)
3456  {
3457  const char *ename = element->GetName();
3458  const char *colon2 = strstr(ename,"::");
3459  if (colon2) ename = colon2+2;
3460  if (element->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kDoNotDelete)) {
3461  if(element->GetArrayLength() <= 1) {
3462  fprintf(file," %s = 0;\n",ename);
3463  } else {
3464  fprintf(file," memset(%s,0,%d);\n",ename,element->GetSize());
3465  }
3466  } else {
3467  if(element->GetArrayLength() <= 1) {
3468  fprintf(file," delete %s; %s = 0;\n",ename,ename);
3469  } else {
3470  fprintf(file," for (Int_t i=0;i<%d;i++) delete %s[i]; memset(%s,0,%d);\n",element->GetArrayLength(),ename,ename,element->GetSize());
3471  }
3472  }
3473  }
3474  if (element->GetType() == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kCharStar) {
3475  const char *ename = element->GetName();
3476  if (element->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kDoNotDelete)) {
3477  fprintf(file," %s = 0;\n",ename);
3478  } else {
3479  fprintf(file," delete [] %s; %s = 0;\n",ename,ename);
3480  }
3481  }
3482  if (TVirtualStreamerInfo::kOffsetP <= element->GetType() && element->GetType() < TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObject ) {
3483  const char *ename = element->GetName();
3484  if (element->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kDoNotDelete)) {
3485  fprintf(file," %s = 0;\n",ename);
3486  } else if (element->HasCounter()) {
3487  fprintf(file," delete %s; %s = 0;\n",ename,ename);
3488  } else {
3489  fprintf(file," delete [] %s; %s = 0;\n",ename,ename);
3490  }
3491  }
3492  if (element->GetType() == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kSTL || element->GetType() == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kSTLp) {
3493  const char *ename = element->GetName();
3494  const char *prefix = "";
3495  if ( element->GetType() == TVirtualStreamerInfo::kSTLp ) {
3496  prefix = "*";
3497  } else if ( element->IsBase() ) {
3498  ename = "this";
3499  }
3500  TClass *cle = element->GetClassPointer();
3501  TVirtualCollectionProxy *proxy = cle ? element->GetClassPointer()->GetCollectionProxy() : 0;
3502  if (!element->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kDoNotDelete) && proxy) {
3503  Int_t stltype = ((TStreamerSTL*)element)->GetSTLtype();
3504 
3505  if (proxy->HasPointers()) {
3506  fprintf(file," std::for_each( (%s %s).rbegin(), (%s %s).rend(), DeleteObjectFunctor() );\n",prefix,ename,prefix,ename);
3507  //fprintf(file," %s::iterator iter;\n");
3508  //fprintf(file," %s::iterator begin = (%s %s).begin();\n");
3509  //fprintf(file," %s::iterator end (%s %s).end();\n");
3510  //fprintf(file," for( iter = begin; iter != end; ++iter) { delete *iter; }\n");
3511  } else {
3512  if (stltype == ROOT::kSTLmap || stltype == ROOT::kSTLmultimap) {
3513  TString enamebasic = TMakeProject::UpdateAssociativeToVector(element->GetTypeNameBasic());
3514  std::vector<std::string> inside;
3515  int nestedLoc;
3516  TClassEdit::GetSplit(enamebasic, inside, nestedLoc, TClassEdit::kLong64);
3517  if (inside[1][inside[1].size()-1]=='*' || inside[2][inside[2].size()-1]=='*') {
3518  fprintf(file," std::for_each( (%s %s).rbegin(), (%s %s).rend(), DeleteObjectFunctor() );\n",prefix,ename,prefix,ename);
3519  }
3520  }
3521  }
3522  }
3523  if ( prefix[0] ) {
3524  fprintf(file," delete %s; %s = 0;\n",ename,ename);
3525  }
3526  }
3527  }
3528 }

3530 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3531 /// Write the Declaration of class.
3532 
3533 void TStreamerInfo::GenerateDeclaration(FILE *fp, FILE *sfp, const TList *subClasses, Bool_t top)
3534 {
3535  if (fClassVersion == -3) {
3536  return;
3537  }
3538 
3539  Bool_t needGenericTemplate = fElements==0 || fElements->GetEntries() == 0;
3540  Bool_t isTemplate = kFALSE;
3541  const char *clname = GetName();
3542  TString template_protoname;
3543  if (strchr(clname, ':')) {
3544  // We might have a namespace in front of the classname.
3545  Int_t len = strlen(clname);
3546  const char *name = clname;
3547  UInt_t nest = 0;
3548  UInt_t pr_pos = 0;
3549  for (Int_t cur = 0; cur < len; ++cur) {
3550  switch (clname[cur]) {
3551  case '<':
3552  ++nest;
3553  pr_pos = cur;
3554  isTemplate = kTRUE;
3555  break;
3556  case '>':
3557  if (nest == 0) { cur = len; continue; } // the name is not well formed, give up.
3558  --nest;
3559  break;
3560  case ':': {
3561  if (nest == 0 && clname[cur+1] == ':') {
3562  // We have a scope
3563  isTemplate = kFALSE;
3564  name = clname + cur + 2;
3565  }
3566  break;
3567  }
3568  }
3569  }

3576  isTemplate = where != 0;
3577  if (isTemplate) {
3578  template_protoname.Append(clname,where-clname);
3579  }
3580  }

3585  fprintf(fp, "#define %s_h\n", templateName.Data());

3599  if (nbase == 1) fprintf(fp," : public %s",ename);
3600  else fprintf(fp," , public %s",ename);
3601  }
3602  fprintf(fp," {\n");
3603

3605  if (subClasses && subClasses->GetEntries()) {
3606  Bool_t needheader = true;
3607 
3608  TIter subnext(subClasses);
3609  TStreamerInfo *subinfo;
3610  Int_t len = strlen(GetName());
3611  while ((subinfo = (TStreamerInfo*)subnext())) {
3612  if (strncmp(GetName(),subinfo->GetName(),len)==0 && (subinfo->GetName()[len]==':') ) {
3613  if (subinfo->GetName()[len+1]==':' && strstr(subinfo->GetName()+len+2,":")==0) {
3614  if (needheader) {
3615  fprintf(fp,"\npublic:\n");
3616  fprintf(fp,"// Nested classes forward declaration.\n");
3617  needheader = false;
3618  }
3619  TString sub_protoname;
3620  UInt_t sub_numberOfClasses = 0;
3621  UInt_t sub_numberOfNamespaces;
3622  if (subinfo->GetClassVersion() == -3) {
3623  sub_numberOfNamespaces = TMakeProject::GenerateClassPrefix(fp, subinfo->GetName() + len+2, kFALSE, sub_protoname, &sub_numberOfClasses, 3);
3624  } else {

3626  fprintf(fp, ";\n");
3627  }
3628

3630  fprintf(fp, "}; // end of class.\n");
3631  }
3632  if (sub_numberOfNamespaces > 0) {
3633  Error("GenerateDeclaration","Nested classes %s thought to be inside a namespace inside the class %s",subinfo->GetName(),GetName());
3634  }
3635  }
3636  }
3637  }
3638  }
3639 
3640  fprintf(fp,"\npublic:\n");
3641  fprintf(fp,"// Nested classes declaration.\n");
3642 
3643  // Generate nested classes.
3644  if (subClasses && subClasses->GetEntries()) {
3645  TIter subnext(subClasses,kIterBackward);
3646  TStreamerInfo *subinfo;
3647  Int_t len = strlen(GetName());
3648  while ((subinfo = (TStreamerInfo*)subnext())) {
3649  if (strncmp(GetName(),subinfo->GetName(),len)==0 && (subinfo->GetName()[len]==':')) {
3650  if (subinfo->GetName()[len+1]==':' && strstr(subinfo->GetName()+len+2,":")==0) {
3651  subinfo->GenerateDeclaration(fp, sfp, subClasses, kFALSE);
3652  }
3653  }
3654  }
3655  }
3656 
3657  fprintf(fp,"\npublic:\n");
3658  fprintf(fp,"// Data Members.\n");
3659 
3660  {
3661  // Generate data members.
3662  TString name(128);
3663  Int_t ltype = 12;
3664  Int_t ldata = 10;
3665  Int_t lt,ld,is;
3666  TString line;
3667  line.Resize(kMaxLen);
3668  next.Reset();
3669  while ((element = (TStreamerElement*)next())) {
3670 
3671  if (element->IsBase()) continue;
3672  const char *ename = element->GetName();
3673 
3674  name = ename;
3675  for (Int_t i=0;i < element->GetArrayDim();i++) {
3676  name += TString::Format("[%d]",element->GetMaxIndex(i));
3677  }
3678  name += ";";
3679  ld = name.Length();
3680 
3681  TString enamebasic = element->GetTypeNameBasic();
3682  if (element->IsA() == TStreamerSTL::Class()) {
3683  // If we have a map, multimap, set or multiset,
3684  // and the key is a class, we need to replace the
3685  // container by a vector since we don't have the
3686  // comparator function.
3687  Int_t stltype = ((TStreamerSTL*)element)->GetSTLtype();
3688  switch (stltype) {
3689  case ROOT::kSTLmap:
3690  case ROOT::kSTLmultimap:

3695  {

3697  }
3698  default:
3699  // nothing to do.
3700  break;

3702  } else if (strncmp(enamebasic.Data(), "auto_ptr<", strlen("auto_ptr<")) == 0) {
3703  enamebasic = TMakeProject::UpdateAssociativeToVector(enamebasic);
3704  }
3705 
3706  lt = enamebasic.Length();
3707 
3708  line = " ";
3709  line += enamebasic;
3710  if (lt>=ltype) ltype = lt+1;
3711 
3712  for (is = 3+lt; is < (3+ltype); ++is) line += ' ';
3713 
3714  line += name;
3715  if (element->IsaPointer() && !strchr(line,'*')) line[2+ltype] = '*';
3716 
3717  if (ld>=ldata) ldata = ld+1;
3718  for (is = 3+ltype+ld; is < (3+ltype+ldata); ++is) line += ' ';
3719 
3720  line += " //";
3721  line += element->GetTitle();
3722  fprintf(fp,"%s\n",line.Data());
3723  }
3724  }
3725  if (needGenericTemplate && isTemplate) {
3726  // Generate default functions, ClassDef and trailer.
3727  fprintf(fp,"\n %s() {\n",protoname.Data());
3728  R__WriteConstructorBody(fp,next);
3729  fprintf(fp," }\n");
3730  fprintf(fp," %s(%s && ) = default;\n",protoname.Data(),protoname.Data());
3731  fprintf(fp," %s(const %s & rhs )\n",protoname.Data(),protoname.Data());
3732  R__WriteMoveConstructorBody(fp,protoname,next);
3733  fprintf(fp," }\n");
3734  fprintf(fp," virtual ~%s() {\n",protoname.Data());
3735  R__WriteDestructorBody(fp,next);
3736  fprintf(fp," }\n\n");
3737 
3738  } else {
3739  // Generate default functions, ClassDef and trailer.
3740  fprintf(fp,"\n %s();\n",protoname.Data());
3741  fprintf(fp," %s(%s && ) = default;\n",protoname.Data(),protoname.Data());

3755  fprintf(sfp,"}\n");

3784 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

3787 UInt_t TStreamerInfo::GenerateIncludes(FILE *fp, char *inclist, const TList *extrainfos)

3799  }
3800 
3801  TString name(1024);
3802  Int_t ltype = 10;

3810  //if (element->IsA() == TStreamerBase::Class()) continue;

3812  const char *colon2 = strstr(ename,"::");

3834  include++;
3835

3860 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3861 /// Generate header file for the class described by this TStreamerInfo
3862 /// the function is called by TFile::MakeProject for each class in the file
3863 
3864 Int_t TStreamerInfo::GenerateHeaderFile(const char *dirname, const TList *subClasses, const TList *extrainfos)
3865 {
3866  // if (fClassVersion == -4) return 0;
3867  if ((fClass && fClass->GetCollectionType()) || TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(GetName())) return 0;
3868  if (strncmp(GetName(),"pair<",strlen("pair<"))==0) return 0;
3869  if (strncmp(GetName(),"auto_ptr<",strlen("auto_ptr<"))==0) return 0;
3870 
3871  TClass *cl = TClass::GetClass(GetName());
3872  if (cl) {
3873  if (cl->HasInterpreterInfo()) return 0; // skip known classes
3874  }
3875  Bool_t isTemplate = kFALSE;
3876  if (strchr(GetName(),':')) {
3877  UInt_t len = strlen(GetName());
3878  UInt_t nest = 0;
3879  UInt_t scope = 0;
3880  for(UInt_t i=len; i>0; --i) {
3881  switch(GetName()[i]) {
3882  case '>': ++nest; if (scope==0) { isTemplate = kTRUE; } break;
3883  case '<': --nest; break;
3884  case ':':

4061 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4062 /// Return the StreamerElement of "datamember" inside our
4063 /// class or any of its base classes.
4064 ///
4065 /// The offset information
4066 /// contained in the StreamerElement is related to its immediately
4067 /// containing class, so we return in 'offset' the offset inside
4068 /// our class.
4069 
4070 TStreamerElement* TStreamerInfo::GetStreamerElement(const char* datamember, Int_t& offset) const
4071 {
4072  if (!fElements) {
4073  return 0;
4074  }
4075 
4076  // Look first at the data members and base classes
4077  // of our class.
4078  TStreamerElement* element = (TStreamerElement*) fElements->FindObject(datamember);
4079  if (element) {
4080  offset = element->GetOffset();
4081  return element;
4082  }
4083 
4084  // Not found, so now try the data members and base classes
4085  // of the base classes of our class.
4086  if (fClass->HasDataMemberInfo()) {
4087  // Our class has a dictionary loaded, use it to search the base classes.
4088  TStreamerElement* base_element = 0;
4089  TBaseClass* base = 0;
4090  TClass* base_cl = 0;
4091  Int_t base_offset = 0;
4092  Int_t local_offset = 0;
4093  TIter nextb(fClass->GetListOfBases());
4094  // Iterate on list of base classes.
4095  while ((base = (TBaseClass*) nextb())) {
4096  base_cl = TClass::GetClass(base->GetName());
4097  base_element = (TStreamerElement*) fElements->FindObject(base->GetName());
4098  if (!base_cl || !base_element) {
4099  continue;
4100  }
4101  base_offset = base_element->GetOffset();
4102  element = ((TStreamerInfo*)base_cl->GetStreamerInfo())->GetStreamerElement(datamember, local_offset);
4103  if (element) {
4104  offset = base_offset + local_offset;
4105  return element;
4106  }
4107  }
4108  } else {
4109  // Our class's dictionary is not loaded. Search through the base class streamer elements.
4110  TIter next(fElements);
4111  TStreamerElement* curelem = 0;
4112  while ((curelem = (TStreamerElement*) next())) {
4113  if (curelem->InheritsFrom(TStreamerBase::Class())) {
4114  TClass* baseClass = curelem->GetClassPointer();
4115  if (!baseClass) {
4116  continue;
4117  }
4118  Int_t base_offset = curelem->GetOffset();
4119  Int_t local_offset = 0;
4120  TStreamerInfo *baseInfo;
4121  if (baseClass->Property() & kIsAbstract) {
4122  baseInfo = (TStreamerInfo*)baseClass->GetStreamerInfoAbstractEmulated();
4123  } else {
4124  baseInfo = (TStreamerInfo*)baseClass->GetStreamerInfo();
4125  }
4126  if (baseInfo) element = baseInfo->GetStreamerElement(datamember, local_offset);
4127  if (element) {
4128  offset = base_offset + local_offset;
4129  return element;
4130  }
4131  }
4132  }
4133  }
4134  return 0;
4135 }

4293 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4294 /// Return value of element i in object at pointer.
4295 /// The function may be called in two ways:
4296 /// - method1 len < 0: i is assumed to be the TStreamerElement number i in StreamerInfo
4297 /// - method2 len >= 0: i is the type, address of variable is directly pointer.
4298 
4299 template <typename T>
4300 T TStreamerInfo::GetTypedValue(char *pointer, Int_t i, Int_t j, Int_t len) const
4301 {
4302  char *ladd;
4303  Int_t atype;
4304  if (len >= 0) {
4305  ladd = pointer;
4306  atype = i;
4307  } else {
4308  if (i < 0) return 0;
4309  ladd = pointer + fCompFull[i]->fOffset;
4310  atype = fCompFull[i]->fNewType;
4311  len = fCompFull[i]->fElem->GetArrayLength();
4312  if (atype == kSTL) {
4313  TClass *newClass = fCompFull[i]->fElem->GetNewClass();
4314  if (newClass == 0) {
4315  newClass = fCompFull[i]->fElem->GetClassPointer();
4316  }
4317  TClass *innerClass = newClass->GetCollectionProxy()->GetValueClass();
4318  if (innerClass) {
4319  return 0; // We don't know which member of the class we would want.
4320  } else {
4321  TVirtualCollectionProxy *proxy = newClass->GetCollectionProxy();
4322  // EDataType is a subset of TStreamerInfo::EReadWrite
4323  atype = (TStreamerInfo::EReadWrite)proxy->GetType();
4324  TVirtualCollectionProxy::TPushPop pop(proxy,ladd);
4325  Int_t nc = proxy->Size();
4326  if (j >= nc) return 0;
4327  char *element_ptr = (char*)proxy->At(j);
4328  return GetTypedValueAux<T>(atype,element_ptr,0,1);
4329  }
4330  }
4331  }
4332  return GetTypedValueAux<T>(atype,ladd,j,len);
4333 }

4393  return GetTypedValueAux<T>(fCompFull[i]->fType,ladd,k,((TStreamerElement*)fCompFull[i]->fElem)->GetArrayLength());

4396 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4397 /// Insert new members as expressed in the array of TSchemaRule(s).
4398 
4399 void TStreamerInfo::InsertArtificialElements(std::vector<const ROOT::TSchemaRule*> &rules)
4400 {
4401  if (rules.empty()) return;
4402 
4403  TIter next(fElements);
4404  UInt_t count = 0;
4405 
4406  for(auto rule : rules) {
4407  if( rule->IsRenameRule() || rule->IsAliasRule() )
4408  continue;
4409  next.Reset();

4411  while ((element = (TStreamerElement*) next())) {
4412  if ( rule->HasTarget( element->GetName() ) ) {
4413 
4414  // Check whether this is an 'attribute' rule.
4415  if ( rule->GetAttributes()[0] != 0 ) {
4416  TString attr( rule->GetAttributes() );
4417  attr.ToLower();
4418  if (attr.Contains("owner")) {
4419  if (attr.Contains("notowner")) {
4420  element->SetBit(TStreamerElement::kDoNotDelete);
4421  } else {
4422  element->ResetBit(TStreamerElement::kDoNotDelete);
4423  }
4424  }
4425 
4426  }
4427  break;
4428  }
4429  }
4430 
4431  // NOTE: Before adding the rule we should check that the source do
4432  // existing in this StreamerInfo.
4433  const TObjArray *sources = rule->GetSource();
4434  TIter input(sources);
4435  TObject *src;
4436  while((src = input())) {
4437  if ( !GetElements()->FindObject(src->GetName()) ) {
4438  // Missing source.
4439 #if 0 // Don't warn about not activating the rule. If don't warn the user can
4440  // have more flexibility in specifying when the rule applies and relying
4441  // on both the version number *and* the presence of the source members.

4449 #endif
4450  break;
4451  }
4452  }
4453 
4454  if (!rule) continue;
4455 
4456  TStreamerArtificial *newel;
4457  typedef std::vector<TStreamerArtificial*> vec_t;
4458  vec_t toAdd;
4459 
4460  if (rule->GetTarget()==0) {
4461  TString newName;

4485  toAdd.push_back(newel);
4486  } else {
4487  // This would be a completely new member (so it would need to be cached)
4488  // TOBEDONE
4489  }
4490  for(Int_t other = 1; other < rule->GetTarget()->GetEntries(); ++other) {
4491  objstr = (TObjString*)(rule->GetTarget()->At(other));
4492  if (objstr) {
4493  newName = objstr->String();

4495  TRealData::GetName(realDataName,dm);
4496  newel = new TStreamerArtificial(realDataName,"",
4497  fClass->GetDataMemberOffset(newName),
4498  TStreamerInfo::kArtificial,
4499  fClass->GetDataMember( newName )->GetTypeName());
4500  toAdd.push_back(newel);
4501  }
4502  }
4503  }
4504  } // For each target of the rule
4505  }
4506  // Now find we with need to add them
4507  TIter s_iter(rule->GetSource());
4508  Int_t loc = -1;
4509  while( TObjString *s = (TObjString*)s_iter() ) {
4510  for(Int_t i = fElements->GetLast(); i >= 0 && (i+1) >= loc; --i) {
4511  if (s->String() == fElements->UncheckedAt(i)->GetName()) {
4512  if (loc == -1 || (i+1)>loc) {
4513  loc = i+1;
4514  }
4515  }
4516  }
4517  }
4518  if (loc == -1) {
4519  // Verify if the last one is not 'skipped'.
4520  for(Int_t i = fElements->GetLast(); i >= 0 && (i+1) >= loc; --i) {
4521  if ( ((TStreamerElement*)fElements->UncheckedAt(i))->GetNewType() != -2 ) {
4522  break;
4523  }
4524  loc = i;
4525  }
4526  }
4527  if (loc == -1) {
4528  for(vec_t::iterator iter = toAdd.begin(); iter != toAdd.end(); ++iter) {
4529  fElements->Add(*iter);
4530  }
4531  } else {
4532  R__TObjArray_InsertAt(fElements, toAdd, loc);
4533  }
4534  } // None of the target of the rule are on file.

4623 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4624 /// An emulated object is created at address obj, if obj is null we
4625 /// allocate memory for the object.
4626 
4627 void* TStreamerInfo::New(void *obj)
4628 {
4629  //???FIX ME: What about varying length array elements?
4630 
4631  char* p = (char*) obj;
4632 
4633  TIter next(fElements);
4634 
4635  if (!p) {
4636  // Allocate and initialize the memory block.
4637  p = new char[fSize];
4638  memset(p, 0, fSize);
4639  }
4640 
4641  next.Reset();
4642  TStreamerElement* element = (TStreamerElement*) next();
4643 
4644  for (; element; element = (TStreamerElement*) next()) {
4645 
4646  // Skip elements which have not been allocated memory.
4647  if (element->GetOffset() == kMissing) {
4648  continue;
4649  }
4650 
4651  // Skip elements for which we do not have any class
4652  // information. FIXME: Document how this could happen.
4653  TClass* cle = element->GetClassPointer();
4654  if (!cle) {
4655  continue;
4656  }
4657 
4658  char* eaddr = p + element->GetOffset();
4659  Int_t etype = element->GetType();
4660 
4661  //cle->GetStreamerInfo(); //necessary in case "->" is not specified
4662 
4663  switch (etype) {
4664 
4665  case kAnyP:
4666  case kObjectP:
4667  case kSTLp:
4668  {
4669  // Initialize array of pointers with null pointers.
4670  char** r = (char**) eaddr;
4671  Int_t len = element->GetArrayLength();
4672  for (Int_t i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
4673  r[i] = 0;
4674  }
4675  }
4676  break;
4677 
4678  case kObjectp:
4679  case kAnyp:
4680  {
4681  // If the option "->" is given in the data member comment field
4682  // it is assumed that the object exists before reading data in,
4683  // so we create an object.
4684  if (cle != TClonesArray::Class()) {
4685  void** r = (void**) eaddr;
4686  *r = cle->New();
4687  } else {
4688  // In the case of a TClonesArray, the class name of
4689  // the contained objects must be specified in the
4690  // data member comment in this format:
4691  // TClonesArray* myVar; //->(className)
4692  const char* title = element->GetTitle();
4693  const char* bracket1 = strrchr(title, '(');
4694  const char* bracket2 = strrchr(title, ')');
4695  if (bracket1 && bracket2 && (bracket2 != (bracket1 + 1))) {
4696  Int_t len = bracket2 - (bracket1 + 1);
4697  char* clonesClass = new char[len+1];
4698  clonesClass[0] = '\0';
4699  strncat(clonesClass, bracket1 + 1, len);
4700  void** r = (void**) eaddr;
4701  *r = (void*) new TClonesArray(clonesClass);
4702  delete[] clonesClass;
4703  } else {
4704  //Warning("New", "No class name found for TClonesArray initializer in data member comment (expected \"//->(className)\"");
4705  void** r = (void**) eaddr;
4706  *r = (void*) new TClonesArray();
4707  }
4708  }
4709  }
4710  break;
4711 
4712  case kBase:
4713  {
4714  if (cle->Property() & kIsAbstract) {
4715  TVirtualStreamerInfo *einfo = cle->GetStreamerInfoAbstractEmulated();
4716  if (einfo) einfo->New(eaddr);
4717  } else {
4718  cle->New(eaddr);
4719  }
4720  break;
4721  }
4722  case kObject:
4723  case kAny:
4724  case kTObject:
4725  case kTString:
4726  case kTNamed:
4727  {
4728  cle->New(eaddr);
4729  }
4730  break;
4731 
4732  case kSTL:
4733  {
4734  if (strcmp(element->GetName(),"This")==0 &&
4735  !cle->GetCollectionProxy()) {
4736  // missing information, avoid infinite loop
4737  // by doing nothing ....
4738  } else {
4739  cle->New(eaddr);
4740  }
4741  }
4742  break;
4743 
4744  case kObject + kOffsetL:
4745  case kAny + kOffsetL:
4746  case kTObject + kOffsetL:
4747  case kTString + kOffsetL:
4748  case kTNamed + kOffsetL:
4749  case kSTL + kOffsetL:
4750  {
4751  Int_t size = cle->Size();
4752  char* r = eaddr;
4753  Int_t len = element->GetArrayLength();
4754  for (Int_t i = 0; i < len; ++i, r += size) {
4755  cle->New(r);
4756  }
4757  }
4758  break;
4759 
4760  } // switch etype
4761  } // for TIter next(fElements)
4762 
4763  for(int nbase = 0; nbase < fNVirtualInfoLoc; ++nbase) {
4764  *(TStreamerInfo**)(p + fVirtualInfoLoc[nbase]) = this;
4765  }
4766  ++fLiveCount;
4767  return p;
4768 }

4818 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4819 /// Internal part of the destructor.
4820 /// Destruct each of the datamembers in the same order
4821 /// as the implicit destructor would.
4822 
4823 void TStreamerInfo::DestructorImpl(void* obj, Bool_t dtorOnly)
4824 {
4825  R__ASSERT(obj != 0);
4826 
4827  char *p = (char*)obj;
4828 
4829  Int_t nelements = fElements->GetEntriesFast();
4830  //for (; ele; ele = (TStreamerElement*) next())
4831  for (Int_t elenum = nelements - 1; elenum >= 0; --elenum) {
4832  TStreamerElement* ele = (TStreamerElement*) fElements->UncheckedAt(elenum);
4833  if (ele->GetOffset() == kMissing) continue;
4834  char* eaddr = p + ele->GetOffset();
4835 
4836 
4837  Int_t etype = ele->GetType();
4838 
4839  switch(etype) {
4840  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kBool: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,Bool_t); continue;
4841  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kChar: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,Char_t); continue;
4842  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kShort: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,Short_t); continue;
4843  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kInt: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,Int_t); continue;
4844  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kLong: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,Long_t); continue;
4845  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kLong64: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,Long64_t); continue;
4846  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kFloat16:
4847  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kFloat: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,Float_t); continue;
4848  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kDouble32:
4849  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kDouble: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,Double_t); continue;
4850  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kUChar: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,UChar_t); continue;
4851  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kUShort: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,UShort_t); continue;
4852  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kUInt: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,UInt_t); continue;
4853  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kULong: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,ULong_t); continue;
4854  case TStreamerInfo::kOffsetP + TStreamerInfo::kULong64:DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,ULong64_t); continue;
4855  case TStreamerInfo::kCharStar: DeleteBasicPointer(eaddr,ele,Char_t); continue;
4856  }
4857 
4858 
4859 
4860  TClass* cle = ele->GetClassPointer();
4861  if (!cle) continue;
4862 
4863 
4864  if (etype == kObjectp || etype == kAnyp) {
4865  // Destroy an array of pre-allocated objects.
4866  Int_t len = ele->GetArrayLength();
4867  if (!len) {
4868  len = 1;
4869  }
4870  void** r = (void**) eaddr;
4871  for (Int_t j = len - 1; j >= 0; --j) {
4872  if (r[j]) {
4873  cle->Destructor(r[j]);
4874  r[j] = 0;
4875  }
4876  }
4877  }
4878 
4879  if ((etype == kObjectP || etype == kAnyP || etype == kSTLp) && !ele->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kDoNotDelete)) {
4880  // Destroy an array of pointers to not-pre-allocated objects.
4881  Int_t len = ele->GetArrayLength();
4882  if (!len) {
4883  len = 1;
4884  }
4885  void** r = (void**) eaddr;
4886  for (Int_t j = len - 1; j >= 0; --j) {
4887  if (r[j]) {
4888  cle->Destructor(r[j]);
4889  r[j] = 0;
4890  }
4891  }
4892  }
4893 
4894  if (etype == kBase) {
4895  if (cle->Property() & kIsAbstract) {
4896  TVirtualStreamerInfo *einfo = cle->GetStreamerInfoAbstractEmulated();
4897  if (einfo) einfo->Destructor(eaddr, kTRUE);
4898  } else {
4899  cle->Destructor(eaddr, kTRUE);
4900  }
4901  }
4902 
4903  if (etype == kObject || etype == kAny ||
4904  etype == kTObject || etype == kTString || etype == kTNamed) {
4905  // A data member is destroyed, but not deleted.
4906  cle->Destructor(eaddr, kTRUE);
4907  }
4908 
4909  if (etype == kSTL) {
4910  // A data member is destroyed, but not deleted.
4911  TVirtualCollectionProxy *pr = cle->GetCollectionProxy();
4912  if (!pr) {
4913  if (strcmp(ele->GetName(),"This")==0) {
4914  // missing information, avoid infinite loop
4915  // by doing nothing ....
4916  } else {
4917  cle->Destructor(eaddr, kTRUE);
4918  }
4919  } else {
4920  if (ele->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kDoNotDelete)) {
4921  TVirtualCollectionProxy::TPushPop env(cle->GetCollectionProxy(), eaddr); // used for both this 'clear' and the 'clear' inside destructor.
4922  cle->GetCollectionProxy()->Clear(); // empty the collection without deleting the pointer
4923  pr->Destructor(eaddr, kTRUE);
4924  } else {
4925  pr->Destructor(eaddr, kTRUE);
4926  }
4927  }
4928  }
4929 
4930  if (etype == kObject + kOffsetL || etype == kAny + kOffsetL ||
4931  etype == kTObject + kOffsetL || etype == kTString + kOffsetL ||
4932  etype == kTNamed + kOffsetL || etype == kSTL + kOffsetL) {
4933  // For a data member which is an array of objects, we
4934  // destroy the objects, but do not delete them.
4935  Int_t len = ele->GetArrayLength();
4936  Int_t size = cle->Size();
4937  char* r = eaddr + (size * (len - 1));
4938  for (Int_t j = len - 1; j >= 0; --j, r -= size) {
4939  cle->Destructor(r, kTRUE);
4940  }
4941  }
4942  } // iter over elements
4943 
4944  if (!dtorOnly) {
4945  delete[] p;
4946  }
4947  --fLiveCount;
4948 }

4950 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4951 /// Emulated destructor for this class.
4952 ///
4953 /// An emulated object is destroyed at address p.
4954 /// Destruct each of the datamembers in the same order
4955 /// as the implicit destructor would.
4956 
4957 void TStreamerInfo::Destructor(void* obj, Bool_t dtorOnly)
4958 {
4959  // Do nothing if passed a null pointer.
4960  if (obj == 0) return;
4961 
4962  char* p = (char*) obj;
4963 
4964  if (!dtorOnly && fNVirtualInfoLoc) {
4965  // !dtorOnly is used to filter out the case where this is called for
4966  // a base class or embedded object of the outer most class.
4967  TStreamerInfo *allocator = *(TStreamerInfo**)(p + fVirtualInfoLoc[0]);
4968  if (allocator != this) {
4969 
4970  Int_t baseoffset = allocator->GetClass()->GetBaseClassOffset(GetClass());
4971 
4972  p -= baseoffset;
4973  allocator->DestructorImpl(p, kFALSE);
4974  return;
4975  }
4976  }
4977  DestructorImpl(p, dtorOnly);
4978 }

5110 
5111 void TStreamerInfo::Streamer(TBuffer &R__b)
5112 {
5113  UInt_t R__s, R__c;
5114  if (R__b.IsReading()) {
5115  Version_t R__v = R__b.ReadVersion(&R__s, &R__c);
5116  fOldVersion = R__v;
5117  if (R__v > 1) {
5118  //R__b.ReadClassBuffer(TStreamerInfo::Class(), this, R__v, R__s, R__c);
5119  R__b.ClassBegin(TStreamerInfo::Class(), R__v);
5120  R__b.ClassMember("TNamed");
5121  TNamed::Streamer(R__b);
5122  fName = TClassEdit::GetLong64_Name( fName.Data() ).c_str();
5123  R__b.ClassMember("fCheckSum","UInt_t");
5124  R__b >> fCheckSum;
5125  R__b.ClassMember("fClassVersion","Int_t");
5126  R__b >> fClassVersion;
5127  fOnFileClassVersion = fClassVersion;
5128  R__b.ClassMember("fElements","TObjArray*");
5129  R__b >> fElements;
5130  R__b.ClassEnd(TStreamerInfo::Class());
5131  R__b.SetBufferOffset(R__s+R__c+sizeof(UInt_t));
5132  ResetBit(kIsCompiled);
5133  ResetBit(kBuildOldUsed);
5134  ResetBit(kBuildRunning);
5135 
5136  if (R__b.GetParent() && R__b.GetVersionOwner() < 50000)
5137  {
5138  // In some older files, the type of the TStreamerElement was not
5139  // as we (now) expect.
5140  Int_t nobjects = fElements->GetEntriesFast();
5141  TClass *basic = TStreamerBasicType::Class();
5142  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nobjects; i++) {
5143  TStreamerElement *el = (TStreamerElement*)fElements->UncheckedAt(i);
5144  TStreamerElement *rel = 0;
5145  if ( el->IsA() == basic ) {
5146  switch (el->GetType()) {
5147  default: break; /* nothing */
5148  case TStreamerInfo::kObject: /*61*/
5149  rel = new TStreamerObject(el->GetName(),el->GetTitle(),el->GetOffset(),el->GetTypeName());
5150  break;
5151  case TStreamerInfo::kAny: /*62*/
5152  rel = new TStreamerObjectAny(el->GetName(),el->GetTitle(),el->GetOffset(),el->GetTypeName());
5153  break;
5154  case TStreamerInfo::kObjectp: /* 63 */
5155  rel = new TStreamerObjectPointer(el->GetName(),el->GetTitle(),el->GetOffset(),el->GetTypeName());
5156  break;
5157  case TStreamerInfo::kObjectP: /* 64 */
5158  rel = new TStreamerObjectPointer(el->GetName(),el->GetTitle(),el->GetOffset(),el->GetTypeName());
5159  break;
5160  case TStreamerInfo::kTString: /* 65 */
5161  rel = new TStreamerObject(el->GetName(),el->GetTitle(),el->GetOffset(),el->GetTypeName());
5162  break;
5163  }
5164  if (rel) {
5165  (*fElements)[i] = rel;
5166  delete el;
5167  }
5168  }
5169  }
5170  }
5171  return;
5172  }
5173  //====process old versions before automatic schema evolution
5174  TNamed::Streamer(R__b);
5175  fName = TClassEdit::GetLong64_Name( fName.Data() ).c_str();
5176  R__b >> fCheckSum;
5177  R__b >> fClassVersion;
5178  fOnFileClassVersion = fClassVersion;
5179  R__b >> fElements;
5180  R__b.CheckByteCount(R__s, R__c, TStreamerInfo::IsA());
5181  } else {
5182  R__c = R__b.WriteVersion(TStreamerInfo::IsA(), kTRUE);
5183  R__b.ClassBegin(TStreamerInfo::Class());
5184  R__b.ClassMember("TNamed");
5185  TNamed::Streamer(R__b);
5186  R__b.ClassMember("fCheckSum","UInt_t");
5187  R__b << fCheckSum;
5188  R__b.ClassMember("fClassVersion","Int_t");
5189  R__b << ((fClassVersion > 0) ? fClassVersion : -fClassVersion);
5190 
5191  //------------------------------------------------------------------------
5192  // Stream only non-artificial streamer elements
5193  //////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5194 
5195  R__b.ClassMember("fElements","TObjArray*");
5196  {
5197  TObjArray elements(fElements->GetEntriesFast());
5198  TStreamerElement *el;
5199  Int_t nobjects = fElements->GetEntriesFast();
5200  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nobjects; i++) {
5201  el = (TStreamerElement *)fElements->UncheckedAt(i);
5202  if (el != 0 && (el->IsA() == TStreamerArtificial::Class() || el->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kRepeat))) {
5203  // skip
5204  } else if (el != 0 && (el->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kCache) && !el->TestBit(TStreamerElement::kWrite))) {
5205  // skip
5206  } else if (el != 0) {
5207  elements.AddLast(el);
5208  }
5209  }
5210  R__b.WriteObjectAny(&elements, TObjArray::Class(), kFALSE);
5211  }
5212  R__b.ClassEnd(TStreamerInfo::Class());
5213  R__b.SetByteCount(R__c, kTRUE);
5214  }
5215 }
